# MyApp — Claude Code project memory
# (Example file. Copy to your repo root as CLAUDE.md and edit. No real secrets here — ever.)

## Commands
- Install: `pnpm install` (pnpm ONLY — never npm/yarn)
- Dev server: `pnpm dev` (http://localhost:3000)
- Test all: `pnpm test` · single: `pnpm test -- -t "name"`
- Lint + types: `pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck` — both must pass before any commit
- NEVER run `pnpm deploy` — CI owns deployment

## Architecture
- `apps/web` — Next.js frontend
- `apps/api` — Fastify backend; all routes in `apps/api/src/routes/`
- `packages/db` — Prisma; ALL database access goes through repositories here
- `packages/shared` — types/utils shared by web and api

## Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode; no `any` without an inline justification comment
- Errors: throw `AppError` subclasses (`packages/shared/errors.ts`), never strings
- Tests colocated: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`; test behavior, not implementation
- Commits: conventional (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`), imperative mood, say WHY

## Environment
- Secrets come from `.env` (git-ignored). Reference as `$VAR_NAME`; never print values.
- Staging API: `https://staging.example.com` with `Authorization: Bearer $STAGING_TOKEN`
- The staging DB is shared with the team — no destructive migrations against it

## Gotchas
- `apps/api` requires Node 20 (breaks on 22) — `.nvmrc` is authoritative
- `packages/db` schema changes need `pnpm db:generate` before types resolve
- E2E tests need the dev server already running

